Kailia Posey, who was best known for appearing on Toddlers and Tiaras, has died aged 16. The TV star’s devastated mum has confirmed the tragic news in a Facebook post. She has asked fans to respect her loved ones’ privacy as they mourn her loss. The cause of death is yet to be confirmed. However, there have been reports of her suffering an incident in Las Vegas. In a heartfelt statement, Kailia’s mum, Marcy Gatterman, confirmed the sad news on Monday. She wrote: "I don’t have words or any thoughts. A beautiful baby girl is gone. "Please give us privacy as we mourn the loss of Kailia. My baby forever." Fans of the TLC show took to Twitter to share their tributes for the late pageant contestant. Jessical519 said: “#KailiaPosey #FlyHigh Arabella amd all of these younger girls lover you and watching you on stage was such a treat. “You're already missed by many.” IamMoon94 added: “That's so sad may her rest in peace #TooYoung #YouWillBeMissed #KailiaPosey #WeLoveYou” Kailia’s last Instagram post showed her smiling and posing on a staircase as she enjoyed a cruise trip. The shot was captioned: “None of your concern :)” DON'T MISS...Kylie Jenner mocked by Lily Allen for lookalike Met Gala wedding gown [LATEST]Nicki Minaj struggles to contain her modesty at Met Gala 2022 [PICTURES]Katy Perry puts on risqué display as she flashes boob at Met Gala [RED CARPET] Other social media users replied to her post in the comments section to share their shock over the tragic news. Kadanbartrockett said: “Can’t even believe this has happened. I’m praying for you guys to get through this. “She always was so kind to all of us. Rest In Peace.” Ms_mays40 added: “I don't want to believe it...Rest Easy beautiful.” Skyladisney_ typed: “My heart is absolutely shattered. “I love and miss you forever, rest easy and fly high kailia.” Kailia appeared on Toddlers & Tiaras in 2012, aged just 5 years old. She became an internet sensation after a GIF of her grinning went viral.